	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><br /><strong>Summoning</strong></p><ul><li><p>You conjure an extradimensional dwelling. Its entrance is a faintly shimmering portal 5 ft. wide and 10 ft. tall. You and creatures you designate may enter while the portal is open. You can open or close the portal from within 30 ft. While closed, the portal is invisible.</p></li><li><p>The mansion consists of up to 50 cubes (10 ft. each side) arranged in any floor plan you choose. The space is fully furnished and decorated as you desire. Furnishings and objects dissipate into smoke if removed.</p></li><li><p>The mansion contains clean air, warmth, and sufficient food to provide a nine-course banquet for up to 100 people.</p></li><li><p>A staff of 100 near-transparent servants attends all who enter. You determine their appearance and attire. They obey your commands completely but cannot Attack or directly harm creatures. They may perform normal household tasks such as serving, fetching, cleaning, mending, lighting fires, or preparing food.</p></li><li><p>Servants may move freely within the mansion but cannot leave it.</p></li><li><p>When the spell ends, all creatures within are expelled into the nearest open spaces outside the entrance.</p></li></ul>",
			"chat": ""
		},
